The paper deals with learning and decision-making in the presence of limited memory and private signals, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of memory and observations of previous decisions also suggests a connection to the field of data structures (cs.DS).
